<h2 id="1000">8. Carrying out the group function</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can use group functions to trigger specific procedures for several customers. For example, this can be sending an email template or printing address labels.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Carrying out the group function:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Customers » Edit customers</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Filter</strong> tab, enter the search term in the search field or set the filter options in the drop-down menus. Pay attention to the information given in table 4 in the chapter <a href="/en/crm/managing-customer-data#1100"><strong>Searching for customers</strong></a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Search</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the customers which you want to use the group function for.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Group function</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select one or several group functions. Pay attention to the information given in table 6.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Apply</strong> to apply the function(s) to the selected customers.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
